how happy you are.
-[darla laughs]

06:17.544 --> 06:22.381
-I gotta second that.
-I think I know how happy
you both are.

06:22.466 --> 06:24.766
-[darla laughs]
-and I'm gonna triple that
and add a hundred.

06:24.885 --> 06:27.519
-Yes, indeed.
-It feels really good
to be home.

06:27.604 --> 06:31.056
It feels good
to have you home.
Better than you know.

06:31.141 --> 06:32.090
Mmm, I know you missed me.

06:32.192 --> 06:33.425
Yeah, you know
I missed you, huh?

06:33.527 --> 06:35.610
I know, pops, trust me.

06:35.729 --> 06:37.863
Well, don't be too sure.
[laughs]

06:37.948 --> 06:41.066
hey, watch your mama
and your baby sister.
I'm gonna go get the truck.

06:41.151 --> 06:44.035
-All right.
-Happy you're back, boy.

06:45.406 --> 06:46.738
[inhales] you okay, mom?

06:46.824 --> 06:48.874
If you want to sit down,
there's a little bench
over there.

06:48.959 --> 06:50.442
I'm okay, baby.

06:50.544 --> 06:52.878
You excited
about the shower today?

06:52.963 --> 06:55.380
Yeah, I wanna see everybody.
I miss them.

06:55.466 --> 06:58.250
I also wanna eat
a lot of aunt vi's food.

06:58.335 --> 07:01.953
Grandma's is good,
but it's different.
I really miss aunt vi.

07:02.055 --> 07:02.954
Aw, she misses you, too.

07:03.056 --> 07:04.506
You didn't get
to see her last time,

07:04.591 --> 07:07.976
-but you will this time,
I promise.
-All right.

07:08.095 --> 07:12.981
-Let's go check on pops
and make sure he has his keys.
-Mmm, okay. [chuckles]

